<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ881006-0165 </DOCNO><HL> Edison Brothers to Post a Gain </HL><SO> </SO><CO> EBS </CO><IN> REL </IN><DATELINE> ST. LOUIS  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Edison Brothers Stores Inc. said it will post a pretax gain of $26.3 million in the fourth quarter from the sale of property.    The retail concern said it agreed to sell the land and building in New York City to Takashimaya Inc. of Japan. Edison, which currently operates a Chandlers shoe store on the site, said the sale is expected to be completed in December.    In the fourth quarter of 1987, the company had a loss of $15.5 million, after restructuring charges, on sales of $304.9 million. </TEXT></DOC>